---
import ConditionPage from '../../components/ConditionPage.astro';
---
<ConditionPage
	title="Treatment in Clapham"
	highlight="Shoulder Pain"
	heroSubtitle="At Balance Performance Physiotherapy, we focus on understanding what's causing your shoulder pain and how we can fix it."
	breadcrumb="Shoulder Pain"
	seoTitle="Shoulder Pain Treatment in Clapham"
	seoDescription="Expert shoulder pain treatment in Clapham. Whether from overload, a fall, or injury, we combine hands-on therapy and targeted rehab to restore confident shoulder use."
	introImage="/condition/shoulder-pain/tennis-serve.jpg"
	whoImage="/condition/shoulder-pain/netball-action.jpg"
	intro={[
		"Whether your shoulder pain has come from movement problems, a fall, overload or an injury, we combine hands-on treatment with targeted rehab to reduce pain, restore mobility and build long-term stability.",
	]}
	symptomsHeading="When to get your shoulder"
	symptomsHighlight="checked"
	symptomsList={[
		"Pain during overhead reaching or lifting activities",
		"Night pain disrupting sleep",
		"Stiffness or limited arm movement",
		"Weakness or heaviness sensations",
		"Instability or shoulder \"giving way\"",
		"Pain radiating into the arm, neck or upper back",
	]}
	treatmentHeading="How we treat"
	treatmentHighlight="shoulder pain"
	treatmentIntro="Treatment may include:"
	treatmentList={[
		"Physiotherapy to improve movement and function",
		"Manual therapy to reduce pain and stiffness",
		"Strength and rehab exercises tailored to your shoulder",
		"Advice on training, work and daily activities",
	]}
	whoHeading="Who we"
	whoHighlight="help"
	whoList={[
		"Gym members and athletes managing overload or injury",
		"Individuals with repetitive or physically demanding jobs",
		"Post-surgery rehabilitation patients (e.g. rotator cuff repairs)",
		"Those experiencing frozen shoulder or weakness",
		"Seniors concerned about functional mobility loss",
	]}
	faqs={[
		{ q: "What is a rotator cuff injury?", a: "It involves the muscles and tendons that support your shoulder. Most cases respond well to targeted strengthening." },
		{ q: "Can you help with frozen shoulder?", a: "Yes. we guide you through each stage with the right mix of movement and treatment." },
		{ q: "Why is my shoulder worse at night?", a: "Positioning and pressure on sensitive structures can increase symptoms." },
		{ q: "Do I need a scan?", a: "Not usually. We can assess your shoulder clinically and refer if needed." },
		{ q: "How long does rehab take?", a: "Many people improve quickly, but building strength and resilience usually takes several weeks." },
		{ q: "Could my shoulder pain be coming from my neck?", a: "Yes. we always check this as part of your assessment." },
	]}
/>
